@ JOSH.INVENTORY

INVENTORY.NAVIRE
  & Navire, my primary workstation, is a Victorian-era Linux laptop with 2GB of RAM and a 1.10 GHz processor. {{Dotfiles|https://github.com/joshavanier/dots}} are available on GitHub.
  * Usage
  & I work offline to minimise distractions and maximise focus. I only go online if I need to research, download, or share something.
  = No idling in front of the computer
  = Focus on one task at a time
  = Only go online if necessary
  * Essentials
  = Browser: {{Firefox|https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/new}}, {{surf|https://surf.suckless.org}}
  = Files: {{ranger|https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Ranger}}, {{nnn|https://github.com/jarun/nnn}}
  = Image compressor: {{optipng|http://optipng.sourceforge.net}}, {{jpegoptim|https://github.com/tjko/jpegoptim}}
  = Image editor: {{GIMP|https://www.gimp.org}}
  = Image viewer: {{feh|https://feh.finalrewind.org}}
  = Media player: {{mpv|https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Mpv}}
  = Metadata cleaner: {{mat|https://github.com/jubalh/MAT}}
  = Music composition: {{Marabu|https://wiki.xxiivv.com/#marabu}}
  = Music player: {{cmus|https://cmus.github.io}}
  = PDF reader: {{zathura|https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Zathura}}
  = Terminal: xterm, {{st|https://st.suckless.org}}
  = Text editor: {{vim|https://www.vim.org}}
  = Vector tool: {{Dotgrid|https://wiki.xxiivv.com/#dotgrid}}
  = WM: {{i3wm|https://i3wm.org}}

